    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-04T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-04T12:00:00-05:00" n="370"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d370">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EAC/7–445: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-04T19:00:00+02:00"
                            >July 4, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6737. Comea 314. Final text agreement on additional requirements agreed today EAC
                    preparatory to signature.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>[At the Tripartite Conference of Berlin, July 17 to August 2, 1945, agreement
                        was reached on the political and economic principles of a coordinated Allied
                        policy toward defeated Germany during the period of Allied control. For text
                        of the agreement, see part III of the Report on the Tripartite Conference of
                        Berlin, released to the press on August 2, 1945, <ref
                            target="frus1945Berlinv02#pg_1501">
                            <hi rend="italic">Conference of Berlin</hi> (<hi rend="italic"
                                >Potsdam</hi>), volume II, pages 1501</ref>–<ref
                            target="frus1945Berlinv02#pg_1505">1505</ref>, or Department of State
                            <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, August 5, 1945, page 154. See also part
                        II of the Protocol of the Proceedings of the Berlin Conference, August 1,
                        1945, <ref target="frus1945Berlinv02#pg_1481">
                            <hi rend="italic">Conference of Berlin</hi> (<hi rend="italic"
                                >Potsdam</hi>), volume II, pages 1481</ref>–<ref
                            target="frus1945Berlinv02#pg_1485">1485</ref>. For additional
                        documentation regarding the principles to govern the treatment of Germany in
                        the initial control period, see <ref target="frus1945Berlinv01#pg_435">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, volume I, pages 435</ref>–<ref
                            target="frus1945Berlinv01#pg_506">506</ref> and <ref
                            target="frus1945Berlinv02#pg_750">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, volume II, pages 750</ref>–<ref
                            target="frus1945Berlinv02#pg_830">830</ref> and <ref
                            target="frus1945Berlinv02#pg_1560">1560</ref>–<ref
                            target="frus1945Berlinv02#pg_1564">1564</ref>, and the Minutes and Other
                        Records of Conference Proceedings, <ref target="frus1945Berlinv02#pg_31">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, pages 31</ref>–<ref
                            target="frus1945Berlinv02#pg_606">606</ref>
                        <hi rend="italic">passim</hi>.</p>
                    <p>An agreement between the Governments of the United States, the Soviet Union,
                        the United Kingdom, and the Provisional Government of the French Republic on
                        certain additional requirements to be imposed on Germany was signed <hi
                            rend="italic">ad referendum</hi> on July 25, 1945, at a meeting of the
                        European Advisory Commission at London. For text of the agreement, together
                        with the accompanying “Report by the European Advisory Commission to the
                        Governments of the United States, the Soviet Union, the United Kingdom, and
                        the Provisional Government of the French Republic” of the same date, see
                            <ref target="frus1945Berlinv02#pg_1008">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, volume II, page 1008</ref> ff. For
                        documentation regarding the negotiation of the agreement on “Additional
                        Requirements”, see <ref target="frus1945Berlinv01#pg_604">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, volume I, pages 604</ref>–<ref
                            target="frus1945Berlinv01#pg_606">606</ref>, <ref
                            target="frus1945Berlinv02#pg_138">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, volume II, pages 138</ref>, <ref
                            target="frus1945Berlinv02#pg_407">407</ref>, <ref
                            target="frus1945Berlinv02#pg_1006">1006</ref>–<ref
                            target="frus1945Berlinv02#pg_1023">1023</ref>.]</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
